2. GITHUB README
🔵 Title:

Web Traffic Conversion Prediction (Imbalanced Classification Problem)

🔵 Overview

This project predicts user conversion behavior using machine learning models on a real-world imbalanced web traffic dataset.

🔵 Workflow
Data Cleaning
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Statistical Testing (Correlation, ANOVA, Chi-square)
Feature Engineering
Handling Class Imbalance (SMOTE)
Model Training (Logistic Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost)
Model Evaluation (Confusion Matrix, ROC-AUC)
Threshold Tuning
🔵 Key Features Engineered
Engagement Score
Session Intensity
High Engagement Flag
Bounce Indicator Transformation
🔵 Models Used
Logistic Regression (Baseline)
Random Forest (Non-linear model)
XGBoost (Advanced boosting model)
🔵 Results Summary
Initial models showed bias toward majority class
SMOTE improved class balance
Feature engineering improved recall
Final model showed trade-off between precision and recall
ROC-AUC indicated weak but learnable signal
🔵 Key Learnings
Accuracy is misleading in imbalanced datasets
Recall and F1-score are more important
Feature engineering significantly impacts model performance
Real-world behavioral data is often noisy and non-linear
🔵 Tech Stack

Python, Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, XGBoost, Imbalanced-learn, Matplotlib
